title: Volcano
tags:
---
Did you know earthquakes can cause both volcanoes and tsunamis? Let me explain how. Earthquakes happen when tectonic plates under the Earth's surface move suddenly. This can release a lot of energy. #line:Volcano1

<<volcano YarnCommand>>

Sometimes, this energy causes magma to rise to the surface, creating a volcano. It's like shaking a bottle of soda — the pressure forces the liquid out. #line:Volcano2

<<tsunami YarnCommand>>

Earthquakes can also cause tsunamis. When the ocean floor moves, it pushes water up, creating giant waves. These waves travel fast and can hit the shore with great force. #line:Volcano3
So, an earthquake under the ocean can cause both volcanic eruptions and tsunamis, making them very dangerous. That's why it's important to study earthquakes — to understand how they affect our planet and to prepare for their impacts. #line:Volcano4

<<teleportSeismo YarnCommand>>

